data.chText: （级别或地位）最高的，至高无上的

data.enText: the Supreme Commander of the armed forces

data.chText: 这个比赛项目她所向无敌。
data.enText: It is an event in which she reigns supreme .
very great or the greatest in degree

data.chText: 作出最大牺牲（为信仰牺牲生命）
data.enText: to make the supreme sacrifice (= die for what you believe in)

data.chText: 她充满自信地微微一笑。

tr: greatest in status or authority or power
final or last in your life or progress

value.def: Supreme is used in the title of a person or an official group to indicate that they are at the highest level in a particular organization or system.

example.ex: MacArthur was Supreme Commander for the allied powers in the Pacific.
example.tran: 麦克阿瑟将军曾是太平洋战区盟军的最高统帅。

value.def: You use supreme to emphasize that a quality or thing is very great.

example.ex: Her approval was of supreme importance...
example.tran: 她的认可是至关重要的。

example.ex: The lady conspired to seize supreme power.
example.tran: 该女士图谋攫取最高权力。

example.ex: We are supremely confident because we have the right mixture of skill and experience...
example.tran: 我们有必备的技巧和经验，因此自信满满。

example.ex: She gets on with her job and does it supremely well.
example.tran: 她继续她的工作,并且做得非常出色。
